
Overview of verb bother

The verb bother has 6 senses (first 3 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (18) trouble oneself, trouble, bother, inconvenience oneself -- (take the trouble to do something; concern oneself; "He did not trouble to call his mother on her birthday"; "Don't bother, please")
2. (16) annoy, rag, get to, bother, get at, irritate, rile, nark, nettle, gravel, vex, chafe, devil -- (cause annoyance in; disturb, especially by minor irritations; "Mosquitoes buzzing in my ear really bothers me"; "It irritates me that she never closes the door after she leaves")
3. (8) trouble, put out, inconvenience, disoblige, discommode, incommode, bother -- (to cause inconvenience or discomfort to; "Sorry to trouble you, but...")
4. bother -- (intrude or enter uninvited; "Don't bother the professor while she is grading term papers")
5. bother -- (make nervous or agitated; "The mere thought of her bothered him and made his heart beat faster")
6. bother -- (make confused or perplexed or puzzled)

